column2: I am a serious feminist.  I spent 5 years working for a women's rights organization.  I have been a supporter of the ACLU for decades.  I believed Amber at first.  Then I watched a lot of the trial, and I listened to the audio recordings of Amber and Johnny.  It's quite clear, not just to me but to most of the world, that she was the abuser in the situation.  This is unusual, of course, given his fame and money, but it's also just painfully, obviously, true, once you look at the evidence.   Everyone can make mistakes - the ACLU, understandably, made a mistake in naming Amber Heard an Ambassador for Women's Rights.   Much of that evidence hadn't been publicly released when the ACLU made a decision.  But correcting mistakes is important.  In this case, the ACLU is losing massive credibility if they stand by Amber Heard, given what we have all seen and heard with our own eyes.  Please don't gaslight your supporters in an effort to not cop to a mistake.  Remove Amber Heard as a Women's Rights Ambassador.

column2: As an childhood sexual abuse survivor and a rape survivor I have PTSD. Seeing the videos and hearing the recordings of Amber was very triggering. She does not show one symptom of PTSD. Even sitting in the court room she doesn't seem to be very good at acting like it. When I came across my abuser in court, I knew he was coming. I never lost knowledge of where he was at. Even though I could never even look at him. She kept looking at Johnny. Why would you want to look at someone that you are afraid of. Plus here recount of the details were so off. I didn't give any extra details. They had to pull it out of me. I just didn't want to talk about it. She seems like she enjoys talking about it. Plus the details that she brings up would not be details that to you would remember and the ones she can't remember are the ones that never leave your mind. IDK it just doesn't add up. Maybe I am being to hard on her. But also the bruises. Like I was bruised for weeks. They were not coverable. Not like she says hers were. And my nose kept making me go cross eyed from swelling for days. No amount of ice and arnica cream takes it away that fast. Trust me. As a hairstylist, I tried.
